<item>
            <title>[MATH-1388] Default number of iterations in integrators</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1388</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;TrapezoidIntegrator&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;MidPointIntegrator&lt;/tt&gt;, the default value for the number of iterations is set to 64.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At iteration 64, the number of points would be 2^63, whereas the &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/Long.html#MAX_VALUE&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;largest positive long value is 2^63 - 1&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even if the default is set to 63, is such a huge value reasonable?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The default value should be defined as a &quot;private&quot; field.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
